exports[`formatBenchmarkMarkdown > matches the golden snapshot so spacing changes are intentional 1`] = `
"## Benchmark 2026-05-01 (build 9815ea5, Linux Ubuntu 25.10, WebKitGTK 2.46)

Scenario: calendar-nav. Question: How much memory does repeated week navigation use?
Datasets: Phase A empty. Phase B benchmark-synth-v1, 1000 events.
Methodology: cold-cold against an isolated benchmark DB; 3000 ms programmatic week-view navigation stress; memory sampled at 200 ms during the workload, then once at +30 s post-workload.

### Memory PSS, MB

| Phase | Dataset | Timepoint | Backend MB | Frontend MB | Network MB | Total MB |
|---|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|
| Phase A | empty | workload peak | 87.0 | 261.0 | 16.0 | 348 |
| Phase B | benchmark-synth-v1, 1000 events | workload peak | 87.0 | 430.0 | 16.0 | 517 |
| Phase A | empty | workload end | 87.0 | 231.0 | 16.0 | 318 |
| Phase B | benchmark-synth-v1, 1000 events | workload end | 87.0 | 400.0 | 16.0 | 487 |
| Phase A | empty | +30s | 87.0 | 191.0 | 16.0 | 278 |
| Phase B | benchmark-synth-v1, 1000 events | +30s | 87.0 | 231.0 | 16.0 | 318 |

Settled floor: Phase A 278 MB at +30s, Phase B 318 MB at +30s. Phase B delta over Phase A: +40 MB at floor, +169 MB at peak."
